\v 1 “\w Stand|strong="H5975"\w* \w up|strong="H5975"\w*, \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w*,\f + \fr 2:1 \ft “Son of man”: this is the way that Ezekiel is usually addressed. In Daniel the term has a meaning relating to the end time, but here it simply refers to Ezekiel's humanity and could also be translated “son of Adam,” since “Adam” means “man.”\f* \w because|strong="H5921"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* want \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w talk|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w you|strong="H5921"\w*,” \w he|strong="H5921"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w me|strong="H5921"\w*.
